{"article_id":"fATB6g44ktJAz0K8","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"1 .","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"Around 9 p.m. on Sunday evening , Health and Human Services employees flipped a switch","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"and the new iteration of Healthcare.gov went live .","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"While enrollment does n't start until next Saturday","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"( November 15 ) ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"this new site now allows shoppers to start browsing plans in advance .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"It looks like this :","depth":2},{"id":7,"text":"2 . This is , arguably , the starting line for Obamacare 's second year .","depth":4},{"id":8,"text":"This is when people are going to start poking around Healthcare.gov ,","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"getting a sense of what is available , what it costs , and whether they want to buy it .","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"Open enrollment this year runs from November 15 through February 15 .","depth":4},{"id":11,"text":"This is a much shorter time frame","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"for people to buy health coverage","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"than they had last year ,","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"when the first-ever sign up period started on October 1","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"and ended March 31 .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"3 . Open enrollment 2015 will be easier than open enrollment 2014 in one big way :","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"Healthcare.gov will likely be a functional website .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"When the website launched in 2014 ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"it barely worked .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"Just six people managed to sign up the first day .","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"Healthcare.gov did n't even have a window shopping option .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"Anybody","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"who had even a slight interest in insurance coverage","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"had to fill out a 76-screen application","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"before ever seeing a price tag .","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"The sign-up process became a giant bottleneck","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"and Healthcare.gov cratered under the crush of shoppers","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"trying to fill out applications .","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"there are two reasons","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"this open enrollment will be harder than the last","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"4 . All signs point toward the 2015 Healthcare.gov launch going smoother .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"The site can handle twice as much traffic","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"as it did last year .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Staff at Health and Human Services have successfully run demonstrations of the application and window shopping processes .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"They have shown , in real time , these parts of the website work","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"- a huge boon to the law .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"Healthcare.gov is , essentially , a store","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"to buy insurance .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"And this enrollment season , it seems like the store will open on time .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"5 . That 's the upside for the Obama administration .","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"But it 's also easy to argue that this enrollment period will actually be harder for Obamacare for two main reasons .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"6 . This open enrollment season , the Obama administration is chasing customers","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"who sat out the 2014 sign-up period -","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"and trying to convince them , on the second go-around , that health insurance is worth the price .","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"The Congressional Budget Office estimates","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"that marketplace enrollment will rise to 13 million in 2015 , a 5 million person leap from those","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"who signed up in 2014 .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"The Obama administration arguably got the low-hanging fruit in 2014 ;","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"the people","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"who really wanted coverage","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"- maybe because they were sick , or more financially stable -","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"bought it .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"This time around , the challenge is greater :","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"getting people","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"who decided last year","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"that they were perfectly happy","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"without insurance","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"to change their minds .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"7 . Obamacare 's second big challenge is re-enrollment :","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"making sure","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"the people","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"who bought insurance last year","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"do it again this year .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"One issue","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"that consumer advocates","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"I talk","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"to worry about","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"is that , last year , people shopped exclusively on price","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"- and bought the cheapest , least-robust coverage .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"That could work against Obamacare :","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"if shoppers did n't like the plan","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"they had last year ,","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"they could decide against buying again this year .","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"There 's also a technical challenge here , too ,","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"as Healthcare.gov has never handled re-enrollments before .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"While HHS sources say","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"they 're confident","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"it will work smoothly ,","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"it 's still a new and untested process .","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"8 . The prices","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"being posted today","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"matter a lot .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"Survey after survey of Obamacare shoppers have shown","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"this information will be the most important part of decisions","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"about whether or not to enroll .","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"`` the test for affordability is how many people sign up next year ''","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"While there are 8 million Americans","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"who thought","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"the health plans in Obamacare were a good deal ,","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"the Kaiser Family Foundation estimates","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"there are 20 million more","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"who decided not to sign up .","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"For many of them , the existing prices were too high ;","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"one survey found","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"that 39 percent of shoppers","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"who did n't buy coverage","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"cited `` the costs are n't worth it '' as the reason .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"`` Eight million people clearly found it affordable ,","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"but there are millions more","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"that did n't buy , ''","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"says the Kaiser Family Foundation 's Larry Levitt .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"`` The test for affordability is how many people enroll next year , and the year after . ''","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":205,"left":109,"right":204,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":109,"left":108,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":108,"left":0,"right":107,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":107,"left":104,"right":106,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":106,"left":105,"right":5,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":105,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":117,"right"